value.value: A portion of phyllome epidermis (PO:0025157) that is part of a leaf (PO:0025034).

definition.value: If you are annotating to this term, please add an additional annotation to vascular leaf (PO:0009025) or non-vascular leaf (PO:0025075), depending on the species. All annotations for angiosperms, gymnosperms, and pteridophytes should go to vascular leaf and all annotations for bryophytes should go to non-vascular leaf.

value.value: A portion of endosperm (PO:0009089) tissue in which the first karyokinetic event is accompanied by the formation of a horizontal wall which divides the embryo sac central cell (PO:0020090) into unequal regions. The larger one is the micropylar chamber in which cytokinesis does not occur and the smaller one is the chalazal chamber.
A portion of leaf epidermis (PO:0006016) that covers the adaxial/upper surface of a leaf (PO:0025034).

definition.value: Used to refer to an adaxial epidermis of an entire leaf. More specific terms exist for leaf lamina adaxial epidermis and petiole adaxial epidermis. If you are annotating to this term, please add an additional annotation to vascular leaf (PO:0009025) or non-vascular leaf (PO:0025075), depending on the species. All annotations for angiosperms, gymnosperms, and pteridophytes should go to vascular leaf and all annotations for bryophytes should go to non-vascular leaf.

value.value: A portion of leaf epidermis (PO:0006016) that covers the abaxial/lower surface of a leaf (PO:0025034).

definition.value: Used to refer to an abaxial epidermis of an entire leaf. More specific terms exist for leaf lamina abaxial epidermis and petiole abaxial epidermis. If you are annotating to this term, please add an additional annotation to vascular leaf (PO:0009025) or non-vascular leaf (PO:0025075), depending on the species. All annotations for angiosperms, gymnosperms, and pteridophytes should go to vascular leaf and all annotations for bryophytes should go to non-vascular leaf.

value.value: A root apical meristem (PO:0020147) that gives rise to a lateral root (PO:0020121).

definition.value: This is different from root lateral meristem.

value.value: A root apical meristem (PO:0020147) that gives rise to a shoot-borne root (PO:0000042).

A portion of ground tissue (PO:0025059) which forms a strip along the leaf veins and extending from the bundle sheath (PO:0006023) to the epidermis. It may be present on one or both sides of the vein and may consist of parenchyma or sclerenchyma.

A portion of ground tissue (PO:0025059) which comprises a layer or layers of cells surrounding the vascular bundles (PO:0005020) of leaves. It may consist of parenchyma (PO:0005421) or sclerenchyma (PO:0005427).
A single layered, parenchymatous bundle sheath characterized by presence of large quantity of starch.

The inner endodermal sheath of a two layered bundle sheath. The cells are smaller in diameter compared to those in outer wall (starch sheath). The cell walls are thick and contain suberized lamellae. They are analogous to endodermis.
An awn that is part of a lemma.
A cardinal organ part (PO:0025001) which is a short, abrupt, flexible point at the apex of the palea (PO:0009038).
A cardinal organ part (PO:0025001) that is the edge of a leaflet (PO:0020049) and the area immediately internally adjacent to it.

definition.value: If you are annotating to this term, please add an additional annotation to vascular leaf (PO:0009025) or non-vascular leaf (PO:0025075), depending on the species. value.value: A portion of plant epidermis (PO:0005679) that is part of a shoot system (PO:0009006) and arises from the meristem L1 layer (PO:0009020).

definition.value: Often interrupted by stomatal complexes (PO:0002000) and other structures. The shoot system epidermis is different from the root epidermis (PO:0006036) in its origin, function and structure.

value.value: A portion of plant epidermis (PO:0005679) that is part of a root (PO:0009005).

definition.value: The root epidermis is different from the shoot epidermis in its origin, function and structure.

value.value: A portion of root epidermis (PO:0006036) that is part of a shoot-borne root (PO:0000042).
A portion of phyllome epidermis (PO:0025157) that is part of a sepal (PO:0009031).
A portion of phyllome epidermis (PO:0025157) that is part of a petal (PO:0009032).
A  multiseriate portion of root epidermis (PO:0006036) found in aerial roots of some monocots. Most of its cells are dead and store water like a sponge.
A portion of plant epidermis (PO:0005679) that is part of an plant ovule integument (PO:0020021).

definition.value: If you are annotating to this structure for Zea mays or other grasses, please also add an annotation to the corresponding floret type. value.value: A portion of endodermis (PO:0000252) that is part of a hypocotyl (PO:0020100).
A portion of parenchyma tissue that is part of a petiole.
A portion of parenchyma tissue that is part of a sepal.
A portion of parenchyma (PO:0005421) tissue that is part of a petal (PO:0009032).
The chloroplast-containing, photosynthetic parenchymatous tissue situated between the two epidermal layers of the leaf or leaf like organs.
The chloroplast-containing, photosynthetic parenchymatous tissue situated between the two epidermal layers of the petal.
The chloroplast-containing, photosynthetic parenchymatous tissue situated between the two epidermal layers of the sepal.
A shoot system meristem (PO:0006079) that is intercalated between two portions of non-meristematic tissue and results in an increase in length as part of primary growth.

definition.value: See subtypes: leaf intercalary meristem (PO:0006346) and stem intercalary meristem (PO:0006347). Not known to occur in roots. Term for primary growth has been requested in GO.

value.value: A portion of phloem (PO:0005417) tissue that develops from the procambium (PO:0025275).

definition.value: In stem or root it is differentiated behind the apical meristem. Primary phloem develops as part of primary growth (GO term for primary growth has been requested).

value.value: A portion of primary phloem (PO:0006075) tissue that has as parts companion cells (PO:0000071, in angiosperms) or albuminous cells (PO:0025412, in gymnosperms) associated with the sieve elements (PO:0025406) and that develops after the protophloem (PO:0006077).

definition.value: Metaphloem develops after a portion of vascular tissue (PO:0009015) has stopped elongating, in the same location as the protophloem, replacing the protophloem. Sieve elements in the metaphloem are larger than in the protophloem. Develops before the secondary phloem, if any is formed.

value.value: A portion of primary phloem (PO:0006075) tissue has as parts the first-formed sieve elements (PO:0025406) at a particular location and does not have companion cells (PO:0000071, in angiosperms) or albuminous cells (PO:0025412, in gymnosperms) associated with the sieve elements.

definition.value: Protophloem is the first primary phloem to develop in any particular location in a portion of vascular tissue (PO:0009015). Sieve elements in the protophloem are smaller than in the metaphloem (PO:0006076). The protophloem usually only lasts a short time before it is replaced by metaphloem.

value.value: A portion of meristem tissue (PO:0009013) that is part of a shoot system (PO:0009006).
A root apical meristem (PO:0020147) that gives rise to a primary root (PO:0020127).
